 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Ashtaroth Solarium</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Yes Jared, that's been fixed.</P><P>Sally, you did catch a bug that Verant has yet to fix, but it's a rare bug. It won't happen often at all. As most people have stated when a person goes LD, they and their pet go into NPC mode, all factions are neutral based from there on out. Though if you attack a person (trust me, pets are bad when they go off on your group, but a fully buffed and SoS'd warrior can tear into a group of casters like you wouldn't believe) or a pet that's in NPC mode, it'll attack you back like any other pissed off NPC. Now, more often than not this little thing is just amusing and you catch it before anything happens to them to gain aggro on your group. On rare occasion however, you will swear up and down that nothing what so ever was done to gain aggro from this person, now NPC. And it's true, you probably didn't do anything. It's just a random random bug that Verant has as of yet been unable to pin down (and it's not exactly TOP of their priority list). </P><P>So no Sally, don't worry, they didn't change anything. You just got real unlucky and it sucked. <img src=icon_smile_sad.gif border=0 align=middle>  But it's definately not the norm.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=205091" target="_blank"><font color=red><font size=5>Ashtaroth Solarium</font id=size5></font id=red></a><BR><i>Nec-Romancer of Innoruuk</i><BR><i>Legends of the Realm</i></font></td>
